edbackModal_main_2533284\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 26, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104wbr1665702758232.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/wbr1665702758232.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/wbr1665702758232.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"wbr1665702758232\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Numeric Strings (C20)\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The default packing code for the Numeric data type is <code class=\"ph codeph\">C20</code>.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"wbr1665702758232__p_d44534e1_d44535e1_d44536e1\">When this is specified, Uniface allows the following properties in numeric fields:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wbr1665702758232__li_d22169e1_d22170e1_d22171e1\">All arithmetic functions\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wbr1665702758232__li_d22172e1_d22173e1_d22174e1\">Fractions (scaling)\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wbr1665702758232__li_d22175e1_d22176e1_d22177e1\">Storage of the decimal point\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wbr1665702758232__li_d22178e1_d22179e1_d22180e1\">Positive and negative values\n </li>\n</ul>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"wbr1665702758232__section_pwm_hk2_ncc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d736186e72\">Scaling</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"wbr1665702758232__p_d44540e1_d44541e1_d44542e1\">The syntax for scaling with the C\n                                packing code is:</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"wbr1665702758232__p_d44543e1_d44544e1_d44545e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">C</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">m</var>{<code class=\"ph codeph\">.</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">n</var>}</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"wbr1665702758232__ul_v5r_3k2_ncc\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wbr1665702758232__li_d22181e1_d22182e1_d22183e1\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">m</var> is the\n                                        total length of the field to be stored in bytes </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wbr1665702758232__li_d22184e1_d22185e1_d22186e1\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">n</var> is the\n                                        (optional) number of digits after the decimal. If\n                                                <var class=\"keyword varname\">n</var> is present, a period\n                                                (<code class=\"ph codeph\">.</code>) must separate\n                                                <var class=\"keyword varname\">n</var> from <var class=\"keyword varname\">m</var>.\n                                </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"wbr1665702758232__p_d44546e1_d44547e1_d44548e1\">Uniface maps the C packing code for\n                                numeric data to the most suitable numeric storage format in the\n                                underlying DBMS.</p>\n<div class=\"note caution note_caution\" id=\"wbr1665702758232__note_bvr_3k2_ncc\"><span class=\"note__title\">CAUTION:</span> Depending on your DBMS and how\n                                the connector maps these packing codes, it may not be possible to\n                                use the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">selectdb</span> with aggregate functions on\n                                character-packed numeric fields.</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ubp1665702661359.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>selectdb</a><p>Calculate aggregate values for specified fields in the database.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533284\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533284\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Numeric Strings (C20) Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 26, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Numeric Strings (C20) The default packing code for the Numeric data type is C20 . When this is specified, Uniface allows the following properties in numeric fields: All arithmetic functions Fractions (scaling) Storage of the decimal point Positive and negative values Scaling The syntax for scaling with the C packing code is: C m { . n } m is the total length of the field to be stored in bytes n is the (optional) number of digits after the decimal. If n is present, a period ( . ) must separate n from m . Uniface maps the C packing code for numeric data to the most suitable numeric storage format in the underlying DBMS. CAUTION: Depending on your DBMS and how the connector maps these packing codes, it may not be possible to use the selectdb with aggregate functions on character-packed numeric fields. Related Links selectdb Calculate aggregate values for specified fields in the database. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}